item.content:encoded:
[slideshow_deploy id='469']

Anna's Gardens is a full service gardening team based in southwest London.

We specialise in restoring and re-turfing lawns, all aspects of plants and planting, major and minor reseeding, leaf removal and total garden clear-out. We carry out general consultation, can advise you about ecologic gardening, and we offer a complete landscaping and design solution. Our maintenance services cover all garden sizes and client budgets, be it regular, seasonal or just a one-off tidy up and include hedge trimming, grass cutting, turfing, fencing, patios and paving, etc. Our team is very experienced and no project is too big and no job is too small.

Annas Team

Annas team will help you with every aspect of your garden and at every stage of any large projects you may wish to undertake. We have fully qualified professional designers on board to help you design the perfect garden, full of natural colour all year round.We frequently advise our clients on positioning and layout, making full use of your existing plants and features so you dont have to spend a packet to get the best from your garden. Please take a look at our porfolio page for more details and check out our testimonials for feedback from our customers.

Our Service Area

We are based inSouth West Londonand regularly carry out work for clients in the Croydon, Kingston, Lambeth, Merton, Richmond, Sutton, Wandsworth, Epsom, Esher, Claygate, Long Ditton, Surbiton, Molesey, Kingston, Barnes, Putney and Fulham areas, but often work further afield as well.

Who Is Anna?

Anna Bole founded her business in the year 2000. Anna is a highly experienced professional gardener and enjoys an excellent reputation with a large, established customer base both in the UK and overseas. After completing a three-year gardening degree and building on her knowledge by working for some of Europe's gardening experts, Anna decided to create her own company to meet what she sees as her clients' needs. Her approach is simple: Provide each customer with high-quality personalized service Having spent many years working as a gardener, I have extensive plant knowledge and experience of hard and soft landscaping techniques including paving, ponds, turf, design, preparation and planting. Since 2006 my small dedicated team, who are specialists in soft and hard landscaping as well as all aspects of garden maintenance, have worked with me to establish Annas Gardens as a recognised leader in garden design and upkeep in South West London. We have a personal approach and take pride in being considerate, reliable, tidy and professional. We always put our clients first and are frequently complimented on for our working manner and approach. We have extensive experience of creating gardens and effective outdoor spaces for a wide variety of domestic and commercial clients. Green as well as green-fingered we try to recycle as much of the waste that we produce as possible - whether by ensuring that green waste is composted or by recycling landscaping materials on site. We recycle all of our office paper, ensure minimal packaging when securing plants for clients and try to send quotes and invoices by email wherever possible. Being local we are able to attend your property at short notice and can keep a regular eye on garden and outside spaces for you to determine whether anything needs doing. Green, as well as green-fingered We take the environment seriously and are an ecologically sound company, recycling as much as we can and always sourcing green products where possible. To put your mind further at rest, we also have full public liability insurance to the value of 1m.

Wayqecha Cloud forest (2012)

New year always comes with new opportunities. By the time you'll read this post I will be far away in Wayqecha Cloud forest Biological Station in Peru studying and working. The station that sits 2950 meters above sea level is considered to be one of the world's most important biodiversity hotspots. Because of it's topographic complexity it is home for exceptional habitats with vast number of species including birds and orchids. Wayqecha is ideal place for observing cloud forest ecology and catch a glimpse of some of the amazing inhabitants.

Cloud Forest Conservation Programme (2012)

We are pleased to announce that December is a month when Anna's Gardens is joining the "Cloud Forest Conservation Programme" in Ecuador. As a volunteer Anna's Gardens will be participating in tree planting, trail maintenance, reasearch activities, sustainable living and food production as well as some community projects in La Hesperia's Biological Station nature reserve in order to help to conserve a part of the Ecuadorian Cloud Forest. Read more aboutCloud Forest Conservation Programme

item.title: Makeover
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Think of it as a tune-up and service for your garden ...

Rather than choosing a full landscape re-design, many of my clients just need a simple makeover. Im talking about their gardens of course: all my customers are lovely just the way they are! It could be that youre having a party out there and need to spruce it up a bit. Maybe youre moving and need to make the property as presentable as possible before those crucial photos are taken by the estate agency? Or it might be that youve been unable to take care of it yourself and now feel daunted by the amount of work necessary to get it all back up to speed. Well, thats what were here for ... With a full garden makeover, well carry out the following for you:
  • Lawns cut and edges trimmed till sharp and clearly defined
  • All shrubs pruned, thinned and shaped to suit adjacent plants
  • Weeds removed from planted areas and hard surfaces
  • Roses pruned back and deadheaded and rose cleaner applied
  • Beds and borders fully forked and left looking fresh and clean
  • Hedges and topiary trimmed to a pristine finish
  • Overgrown perennials lifted and transplanted as appropriate to specific variety, cut back or staked and tidied
  • Seasonal bedding cleaned, freshened and fed
  • All plantings given organic manure compost and granular feed
  • Climbers pruned appropriately, trained and tied in
  • Young tree canopies raised, dead wooded, tied and staked
  • Fruit trees/bushes canopy thinned, raised and dead wooded
  • Leaves and debris removed from drain hoppers
  • Leaves and other debris cleared from all garden areas
  • Paths & driveways swept and left clean, safe and immaculate
By using our experience and a pair of objective eyes, we can often tweak the layout of your existing plants to give your garden a fresh and totally new look. By simply grouping complementary plants, colours and shapes, we can help you get the most out of what you already have. This is one of the most rewarding aspects of our work, as we create something new and special with the clients input and the look on their faces afterwards is always a pleasure! Its always worth remembering that great gardens cant be achieved overnight and changes might take a whole season to take full effect. With this in mind, on-going care should be provided to ensure the end result is as stunning as we know it can be.

item.title: Garden Maintenance
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
A personal touch is the lifeblood of any garden and really brings it to life ...

Every garden is different and they all have their own unique personality, often as not reflecting that of their owner. In the same way that dog owners are said to eventually resemble their pets, a warm and welcoming garden says a lot about the person that cultivates it. My team is experienced, friendly, highly reliable and very professional and they treat every garden they tend as if it were their own. Our maintenance service includes the following:
  • Mowing and edging
  • Weed Control
  • Fertilization
  • Replanting
  • Leaf Removal
  • Bed Care & Mulching
  • Tree & Shrub Care
  • Aeration De-thatching
  • Power Washing
We arrange a date and time with you and we stick to it and we dont leave until were done. We take great care in our work and will not only carry out all the tasks listed above, but well also make personal recommendations that we think you would like in order to maximise your enjoyment from the garden. With regular visits working to an agreed plan, within a relatively short space of time youll really see your outdoor space bloom and blossom and become the garden you always dreamt it could be. Starting from the most drastic situation, we guarantee to turn things round so that youll have a garden you can be proud of ... because we take pride in everything we do. By keeping on top of things and regularly caring for your plants, lawns and beds, youll soon begin to reap the rewards of a great garden and before you know it, youll find you have an extra room to enjoy in, or rather outside your house!

For when you need more than just an initial makeover and maintenance ...

If youre ready for a total transformation, we can offer a bespoke garden design service that will last a lifetime. Working in consultation with you from the off, well strive to produce the garden of your dreams, whether its an urban back yard, a sizeable tract or an all-out estate. You might want something rich and sophisticated, bursting with seasonal colour. Or you could be looking for a peaceful sanctuary in Mother Natures arms. Maybe a rolling meadow, or a fragrant knot garden would tickle your fancy, or how about a designer courtyard for entertaining on warm summer evenings. Our landscaping team are well versed in both hard and soft environments and are experienced in a number of materials, textures, plants, grasses, blooms, furniture and more, so much more ... The possibilities are limited only by our imaginations ...

item.title: Pots and Window Boxes
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
A lack of space is no excuse for a lack of effort ...

As the world shrinks around us, so too do the green spaces between. Make a stand now and start gardening! It could be that youve never sunk your fingers into soil before, that youve never handled a trowel in your life, or that you simply dont know where to begin. Fear not, for we can help you with even the simplest of gardening tasks: the humble pot and the classic window box. If you live in a smaller space, what better way to make it seem bigger and more alive than by the use of plants and flowers? Do you have a small terrace or balcony? Maybe you have just a patio out the back and a couple of windowsills? You can still have a constant display of colours you can be proud of! We can design, source, plant and install window boxes, balcony, roof terrace and patio gardens on a seasonable cycle so that you can enjoy even the smallest space all year round. Its never too late to get green fingers ...

item.title: Garden Design
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
The full design process broken down into stages ...

Knowing Me, Knowing You

Upon getting in touch for an initial consultation, well arrange to meet you and discuss your garden and introduce you to the way we work. At this stage, well find out your tastes and requirements, while also noting any potential issues with the space in question with a view to creating a brief. Following on from that, well go away and come up with some plans and a quote for the first stage of the design so you know where you are with everything.

Garden Survey

An accurate survey will be needed before we can undertake any real design work and will generally be completed by ourselves. On occasion, well employ a land surveyor for larger, more complicated plots. The survey will detail the buildings, boundaries, existing features and levels required for the preparation of the new garden design.

Outline Plan

The design is made up of an overall artists impression, or mock-up, along with several additional pictures to allow you to fully visualise the finished project. The plan acts as a test bed, so we can talk through in detail what were going to do and make any changes if necessary. It will also act as a blueprint for project phasing if needs be.

Layout Plan Construction Drawings

The Layout Plan will include all the details from which a landscape contractor will cost, set out and actually build the garden. Additional drawings may be needed for specific areas and features, and will be appended to the main Layout Plan.

Planting Plan

The Planting Plan details the locations and settings of all the plants, both old and new. An accompanying Schedule will further list the different plant names, sizes and quantities for costing and ordering as well as their actual placement in the design.

item.title: Preparing Your Lawn For Summer
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
To enjoy your lawn during a long, glorious summer, you really need to start preparing it in spring, with March being the month the serious work begins.
The rake comes into its own as all leaves and surface rubbish need to be removed. Its a good time to think about grass seed and fertilizer so keep an eye out for special offers at your local retailers. Also have a look at your mowers and strimmers to ensure theyre in good working order. Once youre all set, remember not to over-water your lawn early on, because allowing the soil to dry out between rain and watering can lead to deeper roots and a healthier lawn in the long term. If you suffered from some heavy winter frosts in your area, its always a good idea to settle the turf of your lawn with some light rolling. You then need to take care with the first cut: dont go all out at first as this can often cause yellowing in the grass itself and isnt good for the ush green Wimbledon look that we all crave! Id recommend just cutting about a quarter of the length of a blade initially. Then maybe apply some moss killer and let nature take its course for a while ...

item.title: My early spring favourites
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Now is the last time to enjoy any varieties of cornus alba you may be cultivating before we cut them back and carry out the spring garden clearance.
These gorgeous ornamental shrubs are richly vibrant and colourful and bring real texture to any landscape. A quick look at helleborus: these lovely border belles need careful attention at this time of year. Dont be tempted to cut the old flowers if you want to see some more of these springtime specials. Another ideal seasonal shrub is Sweet Box, or sarcococca confusa. This reliable plant is highly adaptable and will grow happily in all conditions from deep shade and dry soil to much sunnier, damper areas. It also has a distinctive fragrance so its a sensory sensation!

item.title: Take A Bough
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This month definitely belongs to the trees and autumn leaves will demand your constant attention, though personally I think theyre beautiful on the tree, on the ground or just falling through the air ...
A splash of bright colours can rock your world this season. Try to imagine a corner of your garden with the towering pampas grass cortaderia selloana, better known as Sunningdale Silver. The Cotinus smoke bush is another beautiful grass that will add a rich, flame-like presence to any area. As winter approaches grasses can really come into their own, aligning themselves in the lee of a breeze, or in calmer corners simply standing proud, highlighted by dew or frost. They can make a big impact on even the simplest of gardens. Before you go rushing off to the garden centre, you might have a bit of work to do as this time of year can also be quite laborious in terms of keeping on top of things. Heres a list of some of the typical chores to be carried out in autumn: Early
  • Put any tender plants under cover before the first frosts arrive
  • Plant or move evergreens and conifers while soil is still warm
  • Plant spring bedding such as wallflowers and polyanthus
  • Plant spring bulbs
  • Plant pots for winter and spring display
Mid
  • Tidy perennials, removing dead stems but leaving seed-heads for birds to eat
  • Plant deciduous trees, shrubs and climbers
  • Lay new lawns providing the soil is not too wet
  • Batten down the hatches, ensuring nothing can blow about or couse damage on windy nights
Aija Putka

item.title: Cloud Forest - La Canoa
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Ecuador is considered one of the 17 mega diverse countries in the world. The nationsdrastic geographic and climatic variations have led to the evolution of thousands ofspecies of flora and fauna. It is home to rain forest, cloud forest, mountains, islands, deserts,valleys and snow capped volcanoes. La Hesperia is a nature reserve located in Ecuador in the Pichincha province, in the western range of the Andes. The station works in natural conservation, combatting deforestation, protecting existing forest, restoring degraded areas andsearching for sustainable activities that enable us to support the reserve and to offer abetter way of life for the local community as well as those who work and live at thereserve. La Hesperia is also striving to becomea model of integrated farming where agricultural practices complement it's primaryobjective of preserving the natural forest.

item.title: Cloud Forest Conservation Programme
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Ecuador is considered one of the 17 mega diverse countries in the world. The nationsdrastic geographic and climatic variations have led to the evolution of thousands ofspecies of flora and fauna. It is home to rain forest, cloud forest, mountains, islands, deserts,valleys and snow capped volcanoes. La Hesperia is a nature reserve located in Ecuador in the Pichincha province, in the western range of the Andes. The station works in natural conservation, combatting deforestation, protecting existing forest, restoring degraded areas andsearching for sustainable activities that enable us to support the reserve and to offer abetter way of life for the local community as well as those who work and live at thereserve. La Hesperia is also striving to becomea model of integrated farming where agricultural practices complement it's primaryobjective of preserving the natural forest.

Some photos from Ecuador

These berries are a vital part in everyday birds diet. You can't not notice the constant police presence in the streets of capital Quito. And seeing it on every corner doesn't necesserely makes you feel safer, no, you feel threatend. Traffic jam in the capital. Mesmerizing view from the window of the dining room. It's a privilege that has been given to the ecotourists-volunteers like me and wich i know will last in my memory forever. Cleaned and off you go for the next round in the forest cleaning. Quito, the capital of Ecuador, founded in 16th century on the ruins of an Inca city. It is the only capital in the world to be directly menaced by an active volcano. Also it is the first city in the world that was named a World Heritage Site by UNESCO. Forest in the fog. Cloud rainforest at an altitude of 2000m, an idyllic place for a lodge. It's a great chance to observe the amazing ecosystem and fauna that the Cloud forest presents. Volunteers live 2-4 people per room. Working schedula - waiking up at 6, breakfast at 7.30,work begans at 8 and finishes at 5pm with lunch break from 12am to 2pm. The wildlife in Ecuador is extremely diverse and fascinating. Banana flower is amongst the most widely consumed foods in South America. Tongarini tree nursery - this is a place were life of a new tree begins.
